init_text: When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And you can't help but notice that while watching their life, you feel like they are completely different from you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "What if this is just a dream?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There, you can see your new life unfold, before it's even begun.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It may be the only way to control your fate, though.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you could never have control forever, but you could have it for a moment.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The movie ends, and you look away.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "No story makes a person who they are," the voice in your head says.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: and you enter the theater again, never to leave.
